[An original letter. autograph throughout. The year-date for this and the four letters of the Amerbach eorrespondence following may be inferred from what is said of the ⁴ conditio’ offered to Amerbaoh—this ean hardly be other than the post of legal adviser to the Strasbourg Couneil. The offer is the subject of several letters between Amerbach and Franz Frosch (the senior legal adviser to the Council) (Am. E.. 92, 93, 99, 103) throughout 1534. On 25 Jan. 1535 Ainerbaoh wrote to Frosch declining (Am. E. 104). Tentative negotiations had taken place in 1533 (see Ep. 2883, and Am.
